			<div class="content" id="post-content-1285900">
									

<p>Dunno if its part of the character or not, but all of the &quot;&#8230;&quot;'s bother me. Ellipsis marks are not toys! Do not abuse them D:</p>
<p>I can't really upvote this one, for two reasons.</p>
<p>1) I just don't think it's in the same quality range as the others. Nothing against you personally Troy.</p>
<p>2) It's so freaking short. Most of the other ones give at least an impression about what's going on. All that's being said here is &quot;You're going to die&quot;. Yes, I realize that's the point, but it's not for the benefit of the orientees, its for the reader. As a reader&#8230;just doesn't give it to me. There's not enough here to really illustrate the dangers, or give any kind of background as to what they'll be doing. This seems more like a staff member talking to security staff that have worked for a while.</p>
<p>Sorry for the wall'o'text, just adding my 2 foundation issue credits.</p>

