														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1285941">
									

<p>Part of it, and I probably undercut myself with some subtly here, is that they're all about to be dosed with amnesiacs. This tale was a bit of an homage to the Lombardi tale <a href="/relationskips">Relationskips</a>, and I try to make reference to what's happening throughout it&#8230; But then again, this also uses my personal canon of how amnesiacs work, too, which is to say: can only kill memory, not the emotions created by that memory, and some things can set those emotions off again. So, for instance, if someone really liked pie, and for God only knows what reason, they had pie erased from their mind, and then later had a piece of pie, they would get a rush of emotion they couldn't explain. Sorry, that's a <em>terrible</em> example, but oh well.</p>
<p>And yeah, the ellipses. Less a character trait and more my attempt to display how intensely uncomfortable he is doing this. He's never done it before, but he's seen it done by the person who regularly does, so&#8230; He's trying. Falling on his face of course, but he's trying.</p>

							</div>

